<br>
A few hints though if you do want to go with the MT strat;<br>
<br>
*Make sure your enchanters cast the deaggression buff on your clerics at the start and an aggression buff on the warrior. <br>
<br>
*Spot heals from the light casters at the start of the fight will save your clerics from catching to much aggression. <br>
<br>
*Make sure that your MT has at least 4 click items for Sont. It will save him from losing all of his buffs in the first 12 seconds. <br>
<br>
*Don't count on slowing either Sont or Kland. Plan on your MT tanking him the whole time unslowed.<br>
<br>
*Make SURE your MT for Sont has 255 fr. If he doesn't he will die from the proc off of Sont's melee attacks.<br>
<br>
Onward to the Doz topic!<br>
<br>
I will gladly give out the sploit on Doz so it can be fixed. If you get him to his front door and jamn him there it stops him from AEing. How can you fix this? Very simple..root Dozer. Want to make this encouter really, really mean? Make sure Doz doesn't warp anywhere but where he spawns when agroed. People will have to work to get casters out of LoS.<br>
<br>
Doz's melee dmg is not predicable. Getting hit for around 900dmg one round and the next round being quaded for close to 4k dmg is in no way predicable (defensive down of course..don't think ive been part of a less then 3 min dozer killing yet). Just because he is slowed doesn't mean he is some mega wuss. <br>
<br>
His AE is what makes him hard not his melee dmg. Having ALL of your melee and anyone in LoS get a 400 dd (unresistable) is hard. Ive seen him just pour out his AE some fights, and other fights his AEs were very few. It's just a matter of luck.<br>
<br>
